{"version":3,"kind":"Article","sha256":"06b976d2a99cae5da9a8e2c608bf9d2b20d7421375e91b3d5c1743a7ff86e429","slug":"rram-devices.index","location":"/rram-devices/index.md","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"RRAM Devices","description":"Resistive RAM, oxide switching, filament formation, sneak currents, crossbar arrays, and in-memory computing.","content_includes_title":false,"exports":[{"format":"md","filename":"index.md","url":"/index-ea82cf008450eedda51036eb454d5cc1.md"}]},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"What is this domain?","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"key":"QMGIlocV3N"}],"identifier":"what-is-this-domain","label":"What is this domain?","html_id":"what-is-this-domain","implicit":true,"key":"jC4PkfLaRZ"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Resistive random-access memory (RRAM) is a class of non-volatile memory technology in which data is stored as the resistance state of a metal-insulator-metal stack. Switching between high-resistance (HRS) and low-resistance (LRS) states is achieved by the formation and dissolution of conductive filaments — typically composed of oxygen vacancies or metal cations — within a thin oxide layer. RRAM devices are among the most mature memristive technologies and have reached commercial production in several forms.","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"kzOspNlIBo"}],"key":"Dtg3TPG7mp"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Why it matters","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"Q5eqHAyM3Q"}],"identifier":"why-it-matters","label":"Why it matters","html_id":"why-it-matters","implicit":true,"key":"S9imssYS4w"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1},"end":{"line":14,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"RRAM offers a compelling combination of properties for neuromorphic computing: nanoscale scalability, CMOS compatibility, analogue conductance tuning, low switching energy, and non-volatility. Dense crossbar arrays of RRAM devices can perform vector-matrix multiplication in the analogue domain at the location of weight storage, eliminating the von Neumann bottleneck and enabling in-memory computing at a fraction of the energy cost of digital approaches.","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1},"end":{"line":14,"column":1}},"key":"FcvpYo6O0L"}],"key":"AVVf8139rh"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Core concepts","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"NutjPOcPdh"}],"identifier":"core-concepts","label":"Core concepts","html_id":"core-concepts","implicit":true,"key":"QQPCUB8ZXt"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Filamentary switching mechanism","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"f8CCcNzEBm"}],"key":"BPe6WkEhIx"},{"type":"text","value":" — set (LRS) and reset (HRS) transitions involve the formation and rupture of nanoscale conductive filaments driven by Joule heating, ion drift, and redox reactions","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"uKm4lJ6eTH"}],"key":"P58pT2rey6"}],"key":"r7OQjuVaWx"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Forming process","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"key":"GHdzzzU36y"}],"key":"XO0mCkW1xV"},{"type":"text","value":" — the initial high-voltage electroforming step that creates the first conductive filament and establishes the switching regime; a source of device-to-device variability","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"key":"HrA0wnJp1J"}],"key":"jZMUHWCwOP"}],"key":"yJEccj0jJw"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Cycle-to-cycle and device-to-device variability","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"key":"SUGAEDIFOh"}],"key":"YDW1mt3IXX"},{"type":"text","value":" — stochastic filament dynamics lead to resistance distributions rather than fixed resistance values, a major challenge for reliable analogue weight storage","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"key":"Qf66iRKBBn"}],"key":"H2JG1NYhJu"}],"key":"cY6oO3qW4J"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1},"end":{"line":21,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1},"end":{"line":21,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Sneak current paths","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1},"end":{"line":21,"column":1}},"key":"ZU5PTeRHIb"}],"key":"vrNAsYw1Z1"},{"type":"text","value":" — in passive crossbar arrays without selector devices, current leaks through